comment:
* The overall status of the Safety Center.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: OVERALL_SEVERITY_LEVEL_UNKNOWN
variables.comment: Indicates the overall severity level of the Safety Center is not currently known.

variables.name: OVERALL_SEVERITY_LEVEL_OK
variables.comment: * Indicates the overall safety status of the device is OK and there are no actionable issues.

variables.name: OVERALL_SEVERITY_LEVEL_RECOMMENDATION
variables.comment: Indicates the presence of safety recommendations which the user is encouraged to act on.

variables.name: OVERALL_SEVERITY_LEVEL_CRITICAL_WARNING
variables.comment: Indicates the presence of critical safety warnings on the device.

variables.name: REFRESH_STATUS_NONE
variables.comment: Indicates that no refresh is ongoing.

variables.name: REFRESH_STATUS_DATA_FETCH_IN_PROGRESS
variables.comment:
* Indicates that a data fetch is ongoing, and Safety Sources are being asked for their current * safety state. * *

If sources already have their safety data cached, they may provide it without triggering a * process to fetch or recompute state which may be expensive and/or slow.

variables.name: REFRESH_STATUS_FULL_RESCAN_IN_PROGRESS
variables.comment:
* Indicates that a full rescan is ongoing, and Safety Sources are being asked to fetch fresh * data for their safety state. * *

The term "fresh" here means that the sources should ensure that the safety data is * accurate as possible at the time of providing it to Safety Center, even if it involves * performing an expensive and/or slow process.

methods.name: public CharSequence getTitle()
methods.comment: Returns the title which describes the overall safety state of the device.

methods.name: public CharSequence getSummary()
methods.comment: Returns the summary text which adds detail to the overall safety state of the device.

methods.name: public int getSeverityLevel()
methods.comment: Returns the current {@link OverallSeverityLevel} of the Safety Center.

methods.name: public int getRefreshStatus()
methods.comment: Returns the current {@link RefreshStatus} of the Safety Center

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
